Title:
Credential Dumping: Local Security Authority (LSA | LSASS.EXE)

Type:
Blog Post

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- This post is a practical walkthrough of dumping and extracting credentials from Windows LSASS (lsass.exe), a high-value process that holds authentication material for interactive sessions.  
- It covers both remote and local approaches using common offensive tooling (lsassy, NetExec/nxc modules, Impacket secretsdump) and built-in/signed utilities (Task Manager, Process Explorer, ProcDump) plus a “fileless” dump method via `rundll32.exe` + `comsvcs.dll` MiniDump.  
- The article explains what credential artifacts can be recovered (NTLM hashes, cleartext passwords in some cases, Kerberos tickets/keys, DPAPI material) and how to parse dumps offline with pypykatz.  
- It also introduces stealthier dumping via nanodump concepts (e.g., indirect syscalls and reduced artifacts) and operational steps like dumping, exfiltration, and cleanup.  
- Defensive sections highlight mitigations (Credential Guard, LSASS PPL, ASR rules) and network/host detection ideas (DRSUAPI/DCSync anomalies, admin share access, RemoteRegistry starts, large SMB transfers).  
- Useful primarily for red teams/pentesters validating post-compromise impact, and for blue teams building detections and hardening guidance around credential theft.

Technical Focus:
- LSASS memory dumping (local vs remote)
- SMB/WMI/RPC-based remote execution and retrieval workflows
- LSA Secrets and registry-based credential material
- DRSUAPI / DCSync via Impacket secretsdump
- Dump parsing with pypykatz (Mimikatz sekurlsa-equivalent)
- Mitigations: Credential Guard, RunAsPPL (LSASS PPL), ASR; detection via service/network telemetry

Use Cases:
- Remote credential harvesting across Windows fleets using NetExec modules (lsassy/nanodump)  
- Extracting NTLM hashes and Kerberos tickets for lateral movement simulations (PtH/PTT)  
- Offline parsing of acquired LSASS dumps during incident response or purple-team exercises  
- Building detections for LSASS dumping tradecraft (admin share writes, RemoteRegistry start, large dump exfil)  
- Validating hardening controls (Credential Guard, PPL) against common dump techniques  

Keywords:
LSASS, LSA, credential dumping, lsassy, NetExec, nxc, CrackMapExec successor, Impacket, secretsdump, DRSUAPI, DCSync, SMB, RemoteRegistry, ProcDump, Process Explorer, Task Manager dump, comsvcs.dll, rundll32, MiniDump, pypykatz, Kerberos TGT, NTLM hash, DPAPI, WDigest, RunAsPPL, Protected Process Light, Credential Guard, ASR rules, Pass-the-Hash, Pass-the-Ticket, nanodump